In the Temple

I stand in the light of the sun,
roots grounding me below,
branches reaching above,
where I may touch the stars,
a gentle temper here,
in the sway of the wild.
I walk the paths laid with stones,
and thorn,
bleed,
yet sing.

— H.D.

- HD
